    <h1>The VTC uProcessor Project (VuPP)</h1>

    <hr/>
    <h2>Overview and History</h2>

    <p>VuPP is a pet project of Peter C. Chapin, a faculty member in the Vermont Technical
    College <a href="http://www.cis.vtc.edu">Computer Information Systems Department</a>. The
    intent of this project is to specify, design, and implement a simple microprocessor from
    scratch. The purpose of this project is to illustrate, in an educational setting, concepts
    of computer architecture, digital design and fabrication, system programming, compiler
    design, and various other related topics. It is my hope that VuPP will eventually be useful
    in a number of classes at VTC both to demonstrate microprocessor concepts in a clear and
    dramatic way as well as to provide a vehicle for student projects. It is also my hope that
    VuPP may eventually prove useful to other educational institutions or to individuals
    interested in learning more about microprocessor systems.</p>

